La franquicia también tiene siete campeonatos de conferencia y 20 campeonatos divisionales, y fue el primer equipo deportivo profesional de las grandes ligas que se basó en San Francisco hace 75 años.

Grupo Fórmula es un conglomerado de medios con más de 90 años de experiencia que ofrece contenido multimedia informativo de diferentes categorías. Radio Fórmula, su división de radio, es el grupo de radio principal en México, con acceso a más de 400 mercados en todo México. El grupo se complementa por: Telefórmula, canal de TV de paga con fuerte influencia y presencia en todo México, así como en los mercados hispanos más grandes de Estados Unidos; PM Onstreet, su medio Out-Of-Home y Formula Online, un ecosistema digital que ofrece una experiencia de usuario extraordinaria al abordar diferentes contenidos en cada plataforma.

In our second episode, we'll put ourselves in the shoes of a scout to understand the qualities they hunt for when they're in the stands, watching the magic unfold on the pitch.

In the third episode, we delve into the intricate process of getting scouted, helping to demystify this crucial, yet often misunderstood, path to a professional football career.

Next, we'll shift our focus to what exactly a player should be working on to pique the interest of scouts. It's not all about scoring goals, you know!

After a successful trial, life can change drastically. We'll give you an insider's view of what happens next in episode five.

Our sixth and seventh episodes are all about the numbers, the stats, the data. We'll investigate how data analysis has revolutionized scouting and why it is now a key player in recruitment decisions.

In episode eight, we're talking metrics. Which ones should players focus on? What numbers matter most to scouts? We'll give you the lowdown on this critical component of the scouting process.

Finally, along with sports psychologist and councellor Neal Trottman, we'll explore other exciting career options in the football business for those who don't make the grade as players. Football is a diverse world, and there are many ways to make your mark.

So, whether you're an aspiring player hoping to catch a scout's eye, a passionate fan wanting to understand the business side of your favourite sport, or just someone who loves a good underdog story, our Journey Into the Scouting World’ has got something for you.

Any questions? Email - drewricemail@gmail.com

Join us as we navigate this fascinating journey into the heartbeat of football. Let's kick off!"
